# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Copy this file to ".env.local" and fill in the values.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Supabase — stores contact-form messages in the "portfolio" table.
# Find these in Supabase: Project Settings → API.
# Use the SERVICE ROLE key (server-side only, keep secret — never expose it
# to the browser). It bypasses Row Level Security so inserts always work.
SUPABASE_URL=https://YOUR-PROJECT-ref.supabase.co
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=your-service-role-key
# Optional: if you prefer the anon key instead, set this and add an INSERT
# RLS policy (see README). The route uses SERVICE_ROLE_KEY first, then this.
# SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-anon-key

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Optional: also email you when someone submits the form.
# If left blank, messages are still saved to Supabase.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# SMTP_HOST=smtp.gmail.com
# SMTP_PORT=587
# SMTP_USER=your-email@gmail.com
# SMTP_PASS=your-app-password
# CONTACT_TO=gayatri.gurugubelli05@gmail.com
